comment_regular_data.body:
Thanks for the direction! I followed the approach in [#11290](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/11290) and it resolved the imgcat issue:
<img width="850" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1270688/189953263-d6b5975f-6014-4778-97f5-3f4bdc912eb8.png">
Of course libvterm doesn't know anything about the size of that image and therefor gets confused where to render next line, but I think this is not important at all at this stage and one can easily create an image viewer plugin for Neovim and take care of this in its own plugin (write new lines, etc).

One problem I noticed with this new approach is rendering hyperlinks explained [here](https://gist.github.com/egmontkob/eb114294efbcd5adb1944c9f3cb5feda)

This command doesn't render a hyperlink in Neovim terminal in iTerm2 (while it works in a normal iTerm2 tab):
```bash
printf "\e]8;;https://neovim.io\e\\A link to Neovim\e]8;;\e\\"
```
while this one does:
```bash
printf "\e]8;;https://neovim.io\e\\A link to Neovim"; sleep .01; printf "\e]8;;\e\\ \n"
```
So I'm thinking with the new approach, maybe we are rendering all osc commands sent in a small time window together and then write "A link to Neovim" in the terminal. Or maybe the opposite (we first write "A link to Neovim" and then osc commands). Is there a way to flush the output buffer after initial osc command and before "A link to Neovim" is written as well as after when it has been written and before the second osc command and make sure it actually gets written in between? I tried this with no luck:
```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/terminal.c b/src/nvim/terminal.c
index 0e6c540bc..3f920710f 100644
--- a/src/nvim/terminal.c
+++ b/src/nvim/terminal.c
@@ -842,6 +842,7 @@ bool terminal_running(const Terminal *term)
 static int term_unhandled_dcs(const char *command, size_t command_length, VTermStringFragment fragment, void *user)
 {
   if (fragment.initial) {
+    ui_call_flush();
     char *buffer = xmalloc(command_length + 3);
     snprintf(buffer, command_length + 3, "\033P%s;", command);
     ui_call_term_unhandled((String){.data = buffer, .size = command_length + 5});
@@ -853,6 +854,7 @@ static int term_unhandled_dcs(const char *command, size_t command_length, VTermS
   }
   if (fragment.final) {
     ui_call_term_unhandled((String){.data = "\033\\", .size = 2});
+    ui_call_flush();
   }
   return 1;
 }
@@ -860,6 +862,7 @@ static int term_unhandled_dcs(const char *command, size_t command_length, VTermS
 static int term_unhandled_osc(int command, VTermStringFragment fragment, void *user)
 {
   if (fragment.initial) {
+    ui_call_flush();
     char *buffer = xmalloc((size_t)((ceil(log10(command))+1)*sizeof(char)));
     int len = sprintf(buffer, "\033]%d;", command);
     ui_call_term_unhandled((String){.data = buffer, .size = (size_t)len});
@@ -871,6 +874,7 @@ static int term_unhandled_osc(int command, VTermStringFragment fragment, void *u
   }
   if (fragment.final) {
     ui_call_term_unhandled((String){.data = "\033\\", .size = 2});
+    ui_call_flush();
   }
   return 1;
 }
